<h1>Development Roadmap: Yehoodi.com</h1>

<div class="grid_16 text alpha">
     <p>Yehoodi 3.0 is a living, breathing entity that we hope will continue to get better and better over time as we roll out new features, based on your suggestions and experiences on the site.  Here is a brief web development roadmap which will give you an idea about what we are already aware of and working on, and when you can expect these improvements to roll out.</p>
</div>
<div class="grid_5 text alpha">
     <h2>Near Term Changes</h2>
     <ul>
          <li><strong>Events:</strong> Ability to submit recurring events (probably just for a limited number of users at first)</li>
          <li><strong>Navigation:</strong> Next and Previous links to facilitate surfing on the site</li>
          <li><strong>Search:</strong> Enhanced search abilities for power users</li>
     </ul>
</div>
<div class="grid_6 text">
     <h2>Medium Term Changes</h2>
     <ul>
          <li><strong>Events:</strong> Ability to say you are attending an event, and see what events your friends are attending</li>
          <li><strong>Events:</strong> Export to Google calendar, iCal, MS Exchange</li>
          <li><strong>Radio:</strong> enhanced Yehoodi Radio player from Dashboard with more meta-info (current DJ, show, etc)</li>
          <li><strong>Friends and Groups:</strong> A way to friend people and to group together like-minded users</li>
          <li><strong>RSS:</strong> Ability to subscribe via RSS to a particular topic or forum</li>
     </ul>
</div>
<div class="grid_5 text omega">
     <h2>Longer Term Changes</h2>
     <ul>
          <li>Enhanced Integration with Facebook, Twitter</li>
          <li>Integration with Google Maps: i.e. world map of all events within a particular date period, get directions to an event, etc.</li>
          <li>Mobile app / mobile web version</li>
          <li>Yehoodi "Pro" Accounts with enhanced abilities</li>
     </ul>
</div>

